# OpenSpec workflow (required)

Use the **official OpenSpec slash commands** in Cursor. Do not implement gameplay without an active change.

## Slash commands (primary)

| Command | When |
|---------|------|
| `/opsx:propose <idea>` | New slice or feature — creates change + all artifacts |
| `/opsx:apply` | Implement `tasks.md` for the active change |
| `/opsx:archive` | After verify + user approval — merge specs and archive |
| `/opsx:explore` | Optional — investigate before proposing |

Default schema: **`roblox-slice`** (set in `openspec/config.yaml`).

## Before writing code

1. Confirm active change: `openspec list` or `openspec/config.yaml` → `workflow.active_change`
2. Run `openspec status --change <name>` — all artifacts must be done before apply
3. For apply: `openspec instructions apply --change <name> --json` then read `contextFiles`
4. Read capability specs in `openspec/specs/` and relevant GDD chapter

## During implementation (`/opsx:apply`)

- Follow `tasks.md` in order; mark `- [x]` immediately after each task
- Register remotes in `Remotes.luau` + Rojo RemoteEvent instances
- Services = business logic; Controllers = UI/input only; Repositories = ProfileStore only
- New features/components = isolated modules (`roblox-feature-modules.mdc`, `docs/Feature-Modules.md`)
- Player-visible strings = localization keys (`roblox-i18n.mdc`); default `en`

## After implementation

- Complete every item in `verify.md`
- `openspec validate <change-name>`
- User approves → `/opsx:archive` (or `openspec archive <name> -y`)
- Update `workflow.active_change` to next slice in Implementation-Plan

## CLI reference

```bash
openspec new change <name>              # uses schema from config.yaml
openspec status --change <name> --json
openspec instructions apply --change <name> --json
openspec validate <name>
openspec archive <name> -y
openspec update                         # refresh Cursor slash commands
```

Never implement gameplay without a spec delta in the change folder.
